UEFI:NTFS — vendored bootloader
================================

`uefi-ntfs.img` in this directory is the UEFI:NTFS bootloader image that Ferrus
writes (raw, `dd`-style) onto the small FAT helper partition (P2) of a Windows
install stick, so that UEFI firmware can boot the NTFS main partition (P1). See
docs/adr/0002-uefi-ntfs-vendoring.md and docs/specs/bootloader.md (SPEC-0005).

How it works
------------
The image is itself a small FAT12 filesystem containing:
  - /EFI/Boot/bootx64.efi   — the UEFI:NTFS loader (and ia32/aa64/arm/riscv64)
  - /EFI/Rufus/ntfs_*.efi    — the NTFS read filesystem driver (+ exFAT drivers)
UEFI firmware runs /EFI/Boot/bootx64.efi from this FAT partition; it loads the
NTFS driver, mounts P1, and chain-loads P1's /efi/boot/bootx64.efi (the Windows
boot manager that Ferrus copies to P1 in Phase 3b).

