Secure Boot (verified, not assumed)
-----------------------------------
The /EFI/Boot/bootx64.efi inside this image is the **Secure Boot-signed** loader.
Verified by byte-for-byte comparison: the bootx64.efi extracted from this image
is identical to the official signed release asset
`bootx64_signed.efi` of pbatard/uefi-ntfs v2.8
(SHA-256 5e22e6209ea557fce49cdbab7d06be4fc99e65d45c4fba01da928e763776bb94),
and differs from the unsigned `bootx64.efi` (SHA-256 f04f3383...). A signed loader
lets the stick boot with Secure Boot enabled.

License and GPL compliance
--------------------------
UEFI:NTFS is licensed under the GNU General Public License v3.0. Ferrus is
GPL-3.0-or-later, so redistributing this binary — including embedding it in the
Ferrus binary via `include_bytes!` — is compatible. The corresponding source is
the upstream repositories pinned above (pbatard/uefi-ntfs; the image is built and
vendored by pbatard/rufus). The repo-root LICENSE carries the full GPLv3 text.

Updating this asset is an explicit, reviewed commit that changes the binary, the
SHA-256 above, and the `UEFI_NTFS_IMG_SHA256` constant in
crates/ferrus-core/src/boot/ together.
